(firstQuint)Anterolateral Versus Posterolateral Approach to the Fractured Hip Arthroplasty.

 The purpose of this study is to compare the anterolateral- to posterolateral approaches in patients suffering a displaced femoral neck fracture operated with an hip arthroplasty.

 Our hypothesis is that the anterolateral approach gives equal or better clinical function, health related quality of life and less complication and reoperations.

